AB  - The purpose of this article is to study some implications of the financial liberalization which is taking place in the European Economic Community (EEC) and is supposed to be completed by the end of 1992. Four aspects are successively tackled: (i) the features of the European Monetary System (EMS) which must be underlined when assessing the process of financial liberalization, (ii) the basic scenarios for the evolution of the EMS, (iii) the positive and normative considerations concerning these scenarios, and (iv) some other implications of the financial liberalization.
